  <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2009 12:41:56 GMT</pubDate>
  <title>RP Log: Valentine&apos;s Blind Date Cecile-Kyril</title>
  <link>http://unnamed-world.livejournal.com/4165.html</link>
  <description>What: &lt;span class=&apos;ljuser ljuser-name_suiko_rpg&apos; lj:user=&apos;suiko_rpg&apos; style=&apos;white-space:nowrap&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&apos;http://suiko-rpg.livejournal.com/profile&apos;&gt;&lt;img src=&apos;http://l-stat.livejournal.com/img/community.gif?v=3&apos; alt=&apos;[info]&apos; width=&apos;16&apos; height=&apos;16&apos; style=&apos;vertical-align: bottom; border: 0; padding-right: 1px;&apos;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&apos;http://suiko-rpg.livejournal.com/&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;suiko_rpg&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; Valentine Blind Date&lt;br /&gt;Who: Cecile and Kyril ( &lt;span class=&apos;ljuser ljuser-name_cmdr_cecile&apos; lj:user=&apos;cmdr_cecile&apos; style=&apos;white-space:nowrap&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&apos;http://cmdr-cecile.livejournal.com/profile&apos;&gt;&lt;img src=&apos;http://l-stat.livejournal.com/img/userinfo.gif?v=3&apos; alt=&apos;[info]&apos; width=&apos;17&apos; height=&apos;17&apos; style=&apos;vertical-align: bottom; border: 0; padding-right: 1px;&apos;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&apos;http://cmdr-cecile.livejournal.com/&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;cmdr_cecile&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and &lt;span class=&apos;ljuser ljuser-name_noble_rage&apos; lj:user=&apos;noble_rage&apos; style=&apos;white-space:nowrap&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&apos;http://noble-rage.livejournal.com/profile&apos;&gt;&lt;img src=&apos;http://l-stat.livejournal.com/img/userinfo.gif?v=3&apos; alt=&apos;[info]&apos; width=&apos;17&apos; height=&apos;17&apos; style=&apos;vertical-align: bottom; border: 0; padding-right: 1px;&apos;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&apos;http://noble-rage.livejournal.com/&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;noble_rage&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;)&lt;br /&gt;When: Snack time... which is anytime.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;cutid1&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Cecile: *sitting at the designated table at the cafe, curiously fiddling with the time and date card*&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: *coming to the cafe in winter outfit and a card in his hand, looking for someone who&apos;s holding the same card. He found a girl sitting on the table* Oh... Hello.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: *swivels around then stands up* Oh! Are you here for the Valentine&apos;s Day activity? *recognizes his card and offers her hand* I&apos;m Cecile, the commander of the guards!! You look familiar, but I&apos;m afraid I don&apos;t remember your name...&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: *glad he finds the right person* Yes, I am. *welcomes Cecile&apos;s hand and smiles* I&apos;m Kyril. I&apos;m always around the castle and see you sometimes. &lt;br /&gt; But I think we never talk...&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: Well you must say hello sometime!! *eager handshake* I&apos;m usually so preoccupied with my patrol, so it is entirely my own fault for not properly introducing myself sooner!! *spins back around and returns to the table* I usually don&apos;t eat here! It&apos;s so kind of them to let us try free food!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: Oh, don&apos;t worry! I do understand you&apos;re busy. *sits into the chair* Yeah, the person who arrange the blind date must be very kind. It has good view, too.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: *hastily removes her helmet and rests it in her lap; it would be awfully impolite to keep it on* I think it is a wonderful way to get to know more people! And clearly it already has helped because now I know who you are! Have you been at Budehuc long? I hope you like it.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: *somehow feels relaxed by talking to Cecile, mostly because of her cheerfulness* Quite a long time ago... around six months. Everybody is nice, thus I can manage to stay comfortably here. Are you from around here, Miss &lt;br /&gt; Cecile?&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: *peers over her menu* Around here? *puffs out proudly* I was &lt;i&gt;born&lt;/i&gt; here! At least, I think so--but I&apos;m almost positive I was!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: *makes a small laugh* Oh, I see... That explains why you seem to love this castle.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: *emphatic nod* But six months... that is still a long time too! Do you feel welcome?&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: Mmm, very. And there are some people from my time, so at least I needn&apos;t to feel alienated. *sits up straighter* Ah, I should be asking about yourself, too. I wouldn&apos;t mind hearing more about you.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: O-oh. *flusters and puts the menu down* But I am really interested to hear more about where you are from too! *pauses in thought* Well, I like to patrol every day, and many nights too; I take Koroku and the other dogs for walks, and I&apos;ve been helping Master Thomas maintain the comment box too!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: Whoa, that&apos;s a lot of things to do... *scratching his cheek* Well, I came from Scarlet Moon -- or known as Toran at this time. I lived with my father&apos;s companions until I misteleported here... *pauses, thinking what he should say next*&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: So many people seem to arrive her accidentally! But it makes me feel like perhaps it&apos;s not so much of an accident, since so many people arrive in the same fashion. *picks out an orange tart from the menu*&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: Well, this is not a bad place to be &apos;lost&apos;. *set down a cup of tea from a waiter infront of Cecile* Weirdly, I&apos;m getting used to see people suddenly come and go here.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: It is a little alarming at first, especially since it was so empty for so long! *eyes the tea curiously* But I hope more people come rather than go... I get attached quickly. *sheepish laugh*&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: Mm, yes, I hope I can meet someone else I know from my time. Oh! Anyway... *takes out a small of confectioneries and hands it to Cecile* I thought I should bring a small present for my &apos;date&apos;, so... Please take it if you don&apos;t mind.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: A gift?! But I didn&apos;t bring you anything... *flusters* I have some ribbons, if you like that sort of thing?&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: *is actually don&apos;t mind of ribbons, but for politeness...* No, that&apos;s okay. A man is supposed to give something to woman at moment like this.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: *tilts her head but shyly accepts the gift* Oh! *takes out an orange-flavored candy* Thank you very much! I, ah--*fumbles through her skirt pockets, then presents him with a shiny yellow ribbon* Ribbons are not just for hair! I hope that you may find something nice to use on.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: Ah... *takes the ribbon and smiles politely* Thank you, I&apos;ll treasure it. And I hope you like the candies, I didn&apos;t what to choose so the shopkeeper gave some recommendations.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: They will help me stay awake during evening patrol! I appreciate it very much. I wish I had known beforehand that you were bringing something... oh.. I feel so rude!!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: It&apos;s really all right, don&apos;t feel that way. You have given me something in return, so that&apos;s OK.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: *tucks away the sweets for her patrol later* I hope that in the future if there is anything I can do for you in return, you will not hesitate to ask! And I hope that we can be friends. *shyly fiddles with her hands* I will make it up to you someday, I promise!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: *beams at her* Sure! And it&apos;ll be nice to have a new friend. I&apos;ll be glad to lend some help for you; knowing you have lot of things to do.&lt;br /&gt; Kyril: Other than patrolling, what do you do at free time?&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: *claps her hands together* Oh! I should take you with me to walk the dogs sometime! I think you would enjoy that. As for free time, hm...I like to carve sometimes, but I&apos;m not very good at it. Sometimes I try to cook, but my soup made Master Thomas ill, so I&apos;ve set aside cooking.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: *sweatdrops at the soup part* I&apos;d be happy to do that!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: Then it&apos;s settled! I am sure the dogs would love you! They are very friendly, although Koichi is a bit adventuresome.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: Oh, haha. Seems I don&apos;t have to worry of being bitten. *small laughs*&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: If they even so much as pull at your socks, they&apos;ll all be in trouble!!! I will see to that!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: *smiles softly* Ahaha, you really like dogs, don&apos;t you.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: They are; they are wonderful friends and are always there to listen! *nods, then after a moment stands and bows* I had a wonderful time meeting you--ah--I think... *rummages around again and presents the rose she was told to give should she like to see the person again* I hope that we can meet again, lots and lots!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: Oh... *receives the rose, totally forgets what it means* Yeah, same here, you&apos;re welcome, Miss Cecile!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: *salutes this time, then puts her helmet back on* Let&apos;s meet again to walk the dogs sometime!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: Mmm, okay! Nice to meet you!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Cecile: *waves and skips off back to her post*&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Kyril: *waves back, looking at the rose before leaving the place too*&lt;a name=&apos;cutid1-end&apos;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;</description>
